ul.li: SAP cloud solutions synchronize their master data with SAP Master Data Integration with the help of master data change requests or change events.
All master changes are stored centrally in the master data event log of SAP Master Data Integration and shared with master data consumers using a distribution model.

li.span: Cloud Integration capabilty within SAP Integration Suite is used for master data integration scenarios between SAP solutions which are not yet supported by SAP Master Data Integration.
SAP Business Accelerator Hub provides predefined integration flows and also APIs, adapters and more to build custom integration flows which are deployed on Cloud Integration.

ul.li: When exchanging master data between SAP Master Data Integration and a third-party solution (cloud, on premise) or SAP on-premise solution Cloud Integration is used, too: It includes a SAP Master Data Integration adapter to synchronize master data with SAP Master Data Integration.

li.font: When exchanging master data with on premise solutions

span.font: it is recommended to also use
SAP Connectivity service with Cloud Connector and Destination service for
span.span: establishing a secure connection from SAP BTP to the on premise landscape.

ul.li: Higher release versions of SAP S/4HANA can also directly synchronize master data with SAP Master Data Integration.
In case the integration scenario involves SAP S/4HANA (or SAP ECC) the SAP Application Interface Framework can enable integration monitoring and error handling for business users.
